value: From Shouchaw, Auh'ui.  Karlbeck No. 467 Feb 1933

Finial of a chariot pole. Bronze, remains of the wooden shaft inside the head.  An almost square tube ending a cap formed like an animal's head, with horns.  There are spiral decorations, and a corroded ring.
Ch’in dynasty (221-206BC) or Period of the Warring States (481-221 BC)

summary_title: Ch’in dynasty or Period of the Warring States
